{
  "stem": "2316.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it destroyed our garden, and it destroyed a few homes, and a few people got-- I don't remember if anyone got killed, but I remember some injuries.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they were flying very, very low, like on top of the roof.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I mean, I was-- we could see the soldiers, the Nazis, inside the plane when we looked up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That's how low they were flying because we didn't have any tall buildings, and, you know, it was just flat homes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was devastating.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean it was just devastating-- mothers, and children, and babies, and cries.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What did they bomb for?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, obviously they were just after the civilians because there was nothing to bomb except the homes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Why would they want to destroy the homes at that time?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They weren't killing the Jews yet, in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that subsided after a while, and everyone went back to their grief and their home and put things in order again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And eventually the Nazis came, took over our town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And while we were there, we already saw refugees coming from Warsaw and from other parts, from Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were running away already from the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, this is unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My parents, my aunts, my uncles, my grandparents, they were planting gardens for next year.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And these refugees are running through the gardens, running through the woods, coming into our shtetl to hide out, and they didn't even stop planting the seeds.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They said, ah they must have done something wrong.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They're running away because they probably did something wrong and they're afraid the Nazis will get them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they just continued like they're going to eat them next spring, or something, like the fruits going to be there, and vegetables.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
